# Conventional Commits

All commits in this repo must follow the [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) spec. This is enforced automatically by `commitlint` via Husky on every commit.

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>
```

- **type** — required, lowercase
- **scope** — optional, lowercase, describes what was changed
- **subject** — required, imperative present tense, no trailing period

## Allowed types

| Type       | When to use                                         |
| ---------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| `feat`     | New feature or behavior visible to the user         |
| `fix`      | Bug fix                                             |
| `docs`     | Documentation only                                  |
| `style`    | Formatting, whitespace — no logic change            |
| `refactor` | Code change that is neither a feat nor a fix        |
| `test`     | Adding or updating tests                            |
| `chore`    | Build process, deps, tooling — no production code   |
| `ci`       | CI/CD configuration files and scripts               |
| `perf`     | Performance improvement                             |
| `revert`   | Reverts a previous commit                           |

## Scope examples (this project)

`auth`, `design`, `infra`, `portfolio`, `outreach`, `portal`, `agents`, `env`, `db`, `ai`

## Examples

```
feat(portfolio): add hero section with CTA
fix(auth): handle expired session token on server
docs(agents): document project rules and conventions (PRO-11)
chore(env): add Gemini API key placeholder to env example
refactor(design): extract token values to CSS custom properties
```

## Breaking changes

Append `!` after the type/scope and add a `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer:

```
feat(auth)!: replace cookie session with JWT

BREAKING CHANGE: existing sessions will be invalidated on deploy
```
